The paper focuses on neural architecture search (NAS) using reinforcement learning and network embedding to generate efficient and resource-constrained architectures for image recognition and keyword spotting problems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of reinforcement learning and network embedding also suggests that the paper may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the keyword spotting problem also suggests that the paper may belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
